This paper discusses the spreading power of nodes in a network, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), network analysis (cs.SI), network dynamics (cs.SD), network science (cs.NI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper specifically mentions social networking and the Internet as examples of different network structures, which further supports the likelihood of it belonging to these sub-categories.
